@startuml Live Game Sync — Timing & Stale State Analysis

title Commander Collector — Live Sync Timing\n(Host + Remote relative to DB, showing stale-state risk)

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam ParticipantPadding 20
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam noteFontSize 11

actor Host as H
participant "Host React\nState" as HS
participant Database as DB
participant "Remote React\nState" as RS
actor Remote as R

== Game Start ==

H -> HS : handleStart(players, life)\nbuildInitialState()\n** sessionCode = null **
note right of HS
  useEffect([state]) fires:
  sessionCode is null → **no DB write**
end note

HS -> DB : createLiveGame(freshState, seats)
DB --> HS : { sessionCode, seats }
HS -> HS : setState adds sessionCode + sessionSeats
note right of HS
  useEffect fires again:
  sessionCode now set → **writes to DB**
  lastWriteTimeRef = now
end note
HS -> DB : updateLiveGame(code, state)

note over DB
  DB now holds: turn=1, currentPlayer=0
  from the **initial** state (no old-game bleed here)
  BUT if deleteLiveGame failed for prior session →
  old session may still be active in DB
end note

== Remote Connects ==

R -> RS : connect(code)\nGET /live-game?code=X
DB --> RS : { is_active:true, state, seat }
RS -> RS : setState(dbState + checkin)\nlastWriteTimeRef = now
RS -> DB : updateLiveGame(code, state+checkin)
note right of RS
  Immediately writes DB state back.
  Write guard blocks poll for 3000ms.
end note

== Steady-State Polling Cycle ==

note over H, R
  POLL_INTERVAL = 3000ms
  Host write guard: 500ms
  Remote write guard: 3000ms
  Heartbeat: 9000ms
end note

group t=0 — Host advances turn (Next Turn button)
  H -> HS : handleNextTurn()
  HS -> HS : currentPlayerIdx++\nturnNumber++\nturnStartTime=now
  HS -> DB : updateLiveGame(code, newState)\n[useEffect on state change]
  HS -> HS : lastWriteTimeRef = now
  note right of HS
    DB is now authoritative:
    turn=2, player=1
  end note
end

group t=200ms — Remote makes an action (e.g. life tap)
  R -> RS : handleLifeChange(idx, -1)
  RS -> RS : setState(prev => { ...prev, life-- })
  note right of RS #ffaaaa
    **STALE DATA WRITE:**
    prev = last polled state (turn=1, player=0)
    Remote has NOT yet seen the host's turn advance.
    life change is correct BUT turnNumber/currentPlayerIdx
    are the old values from last poll.
  end note
  RS -> DB : updateLiveGame(code, { turn=1, player=0, life-- })
  RS -> RS : lastWriteTimeRef = now
  note right of RS
    Write guard now blocks remote poll for 3000ms
  end note
end

group t=500ms — Host poll fires (500ms write guard passes)
  HS -> DB : GET /live-game?code=X
  DB --> HS : { updated_at: T2, state: { turn=1, player=0, life-- } }
  note right of HS #ffaaaa
    updated_at changed (remote wrote at t=200ms).
    JSON differs → host APPLIES the remote state.
    **HOST IS REVERTED** to turn=1, player=0.
  end note
  HS -> HS : setState(remoteStaleState)
  HS -> DB : updateLiveGame(code, revertedState)
end

group t=3200ms — Remote poll finally fires (3000ms guard passes)
  RS -> DB : GET /live-game?code=X
  DB --> RS : { state: { turn=1, player=0, life-- } }
  note right of RS
    Gets the host-reverted state.
    Looks consistent to remote — no visible change.
  end note
end

== Heartbeat (every 9000ms) — FIXED ==

group t=9000ms — Remote heartbeat
  RS -> DB : GET /live-game?code=X\n[read-modify-write]
  DB --> RS : { state: currentDBState }
  note right of RS #aaffaa
    Uses fresh DB state as base — not local prev.
    Only adds remoteCheckins timestamp on top.
    **Does NOT overwrite host turn.**
  end note
  RS -> DB : updateLiveGame(code,\n  { ...currentDBState, remoteCheckins: {..., seat: now} })
end

== Root Cause: Stale Local State on Remote Actions ==

note over HS, RS #ffffaa
  The heartbeat race is fixed.
  But ALL other remote action handlers (life, poison,
  commander damage, pass turn, etc.) still write
  **local React state** to DB — not a fresh DB read.

  If remote local state is behind the host by even one
  poll cycle (up to 3000ms), any remote tap overwrites
  the host's most recent changes in DB.

  The host's 500ms write guard means it polls quickly
  after its own writes, and when it sees the remote's
  stale write (updated_at changed), it applies it,
  reverting its own state.
end note

== Old Game State Scenario ==

note over H, DB #ffd0d0
  Risk: if deleteLiveGame() fails (fire-and-forget, silent catch)
  when starting a new game, the old session remains active.

  If the remote re-scans the same QR or navigates back to the
  same URL code, it connects to the OLD session. Actions on the
  old session do not affect the new game, but the remote player
  sees stale game data (old players, old life totals, old turn).

  Also: host localStorage can hold a game with sessionCode from
  a prior session that was never properly deleted. On page reload,
  loadSavedState() restores this state, and useEffect immediately
  writes it to DB if sessionCode is still active — potentially
  overwriting whatever state is currently in DB.
end note

@enduml
